   - GitLab OAuth authentication flow with `allowGroups` restriction
   - `GET /groups/:id` GitLab REST API endpoint (supports URL-encoded path for subgroups like `group1%2Fsubgroup2`)
   - `url.PathEscape()` for encoding group paths with slashes
   - Go overlay filesystem (`-overlay=file.json`) to substitute files during build/test without modifying originals
   - Go module cache (`GOMODCACHE`) and VCS cache lock files
   - `-modfile=` flag to use a custom `go.mod`
   - `GONOSUMDB=*` to skip sum database verification
   - `gitlab.HTTPErrorCode(err)` to distinguish 404/403 errors from real errors
   - `gitlab.NewHTTPError(code, body)` for creating mock HTTP errors
   - `MockGetGroupByPath` mock variable pattern (same as existing `MockGetGroupsByIDs`)

